@startuml
title Optimisation Retrial Flow

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam sequenceActorBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceActorBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam noteBorderColor #A5B4FC
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #EEF2FF

actor "User & OEX " as Caller
participant "OGW" as OGW
participant "OSB MS" as OSB
participant "NGW" as NGW
participant "OC MS" as OCMS
database "OC MS DB" as OCDB
queue "OC MS Outbox" as Outbox
queue "Kafka" as Kafka
participant "Python/Gurobi\nWorker" as Worker

== Retrial Request ==

Caller -> OGW : 1. POST /optimisation/{id}/retrial\n(If-Match header)
OGW -> OGW : 2. Authenticate caller/token/session\nand derive user context
note right of OGW
User context may include tenant, claims,
roles/scopes, and entitlements.
end note

OGW -> OSB : 3. Invoke OSB MS\nwith user context\nmTLS, correlation id, trace context
OSB -> OSB : 4. Validate user context and runtime state\nExpose retrial action only if allowed
note right of OSB
User-context-related authorisation is performed
at OSB / OCB-level before the request crosses NGW.
end note

OSB -> NGW : 5. Forward retrial request\nwith system caller identity\nmTLS, correlation id, trace context, If-Match\n(no user context downstream)
note right of NGW
User context terminates at NGW.
NGW-to-downstream calls carry only
system/service caller identity plus technical metadata.
end note

NGW -> OCMS : 6. Route retrial request\nusing mTLS and service/system auth context only
note right of OCMS
OC MS authorises the calling service/system.
OC MS does not receive or depend on
end-user identity/claims/roles/scopes.
end note

== Validation ==

OCMS -> OCDB : 7. Validate original Optimisation\nlifecycleStatus = FAILED
OCDB --> OCMS : FAILED status confirmed

== New Optimisation Creation ==

OCMS -> OCDB : 8. Create new Optimisation resource
note right of OCDB
9. New Optimisation links to original
via retrialOf reference.

10. lifecycleStatus = ACKNOWLEDGED
end note
OCDB --> OCMS : New Optimisation persisted

== Event Publishing ==

OCMS -> Outbox : 11. Write OptimisationRequestedEvent\n(instruction = EXECUTE) for new Optimisation\n-- same transaction
Outbox -> Kafka : 12. Relay publishes event to Kafka\nwith correlation id and trace context

== Worker Execution ==

Kafka -> Worker : 13. Python/Gurobi Worker consumes\nand processes new request

== Retrial Boundary ==

note over OCMS, OCDB
14. Original FAILED Optimisation remains FAILED.
Retrial does NOT move it back to PROCESSING.
Only the new Optimisation progresses through the lifecycle.
end note

@enduml
